snippet.textDisplay:
Well this will be my confession...

I was a hater of Bieber since he came out (I was even hesitant to watch this short documentary as well, but I am happy I did), I was having a sort of identity issue back in those times (as a 8-9 year old, yes)and not being able to get along with my girl friends as a girl made me hate all the popular things among them. I just didn't realise this and hated Bieber and also One Direction for no legit reason for a long time. I would find excuses to hate him. He would be spitting on his fans, doing very inappropriate things. But now I see, he was a child going through a big pressure, AS A YOUNG PERSON. Now as I watched this short documentary, I see that he begin maturing, it was very sweet to see his wife talking supportive about him and always standing by him, didn't think this was a serious marriage at first, but now I see that why they are together. I really appreciate how he worked through and succeeded. Well this is all I can say now, and wish good luck in his further career.
